RePlay - Privacy Policy v1.0
Effective Date: Wednesday 18th June 2026
Author: StringShot

Introduction

This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, & protect your information when you use the platform.
By using the service, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
If you do not agree, you must stop using the platform.

Information We Collect

We may collect the following types of information:

Usernames, passwords(encrypted), email addresses, profile settings, supporter tier status, pages you visit on the platform, features you use, time spent on the platform, device type & operating system, IP address (for security usage and abuse prevention, will be encrypted when not needed), videos, 3D models, 3D scenes, animations, images & metadata(for security usage, encrypted when not needed).
You retain ownership of all content you upload.

Your payment information is handled by third-party payment processors.

We do NOT store:

Credit card numbers & bank details.
We only receive confirmation of successful or failed payments.

We use cookies and local storage to:

Keep you logged in, remember preferences, improve performance & display advertisements & sponsorships.
You may disable cookies, but some features may no longer work.

How We Use Your Information

We use your information to:

Operate and maintain the platform, display your content, provide account features, process payments, prevent fraud & abuse, improve performance, personalise your experience, display non‑intrusive ads, provide customer support.
We do not sell your personal data.

Advertising

The platform uses:

Banner ads, sidebar ads & non‑blocking pop‑ups.

We do not use:

Video ads, full‑screen ads & forced‑watch ads.

Supporter tiers may remove ads.
We do not share your personal data with advertisers.

Sharing Your Information

We may share your information only with:

Payment processors (for supporter tiers and marketplace purchases), security services (to prevent fraud, abuse, or attacks), legal authorities (only when required by law) & cloud hosting providers (to store your content securely).

We do not sell or trade your information.
